Post anything that you want, and post it anonymously. Anything. A story, a secret, a confession, a fear, a love -- anything. Be sure to post honestly. Post twice if you'd like. Three times. Four. Then, put this in your LJ to see what your friends (and perhaps others who you don't even realize read your LJ) have to say. IP addresses aren't being logged, so don't worry.

My head is a padded room in a psych ward. It's me and my boxes full of memories. I have one bed and my walls have writing all over them that I wrote when I was drugged up (the nurse gives me drugs to calm me down) and now I can't remember what they mean. I'm all alone in this room/head. I'm not allowed to keep anything sharp, so I can only have the pleasant memories. The nurse that gives me the drugs takes the unhappy memories away from me. Afraid I'll torture or kill myself with them. But. . . I have a loose floorboard in my room. And I hide my unhappy memories in it, waiting for the day when I can use them to kill myself. On the bright side, I get to bounce off the walls! WHEE! *bounces*. . . The writing on the walls. . . sometimes when I'm asleep, I understand them, and they have all the answers that I'm searching for. They're right there in front of me, but I can't translate them. And the boxes are full of memories for anyone to root through. . . I live in a padded room!

What is your head?

Hello! I'm bored. . .

ok. . . bye!

You know when you're bursting with things to say, but you don't think anyone will listen or want to hear it? It's terrible.

Like. . . When I need a shoulder to cry on, I think no one wants to hear it, and I get bitter about it, and I take it out on whoever is around that I wish I could cry to the most. Why? Why don't you want to hear it?

What do you know about Mayan Indians? I'm seriously lonely. It's not fair. Lonlier than I would be if I were all alone. I hate winter. I wish I could hybernate like a bear. Only not like a bear. I have no desire to wake up. . . until I'm dead. I like sleeping. Sleeping isn't lonely.

It's like a bad dream. Or even a good dream that one can't remember. My head is made up of memories. Mostly useless delusions. Why go back? The words get confused and the meanings get changed. So why do we try to communicate, anyway? Let go. Why go back? As they say 'this place is void of all passion'. . . Usually I don't listen to them, but this time they're not wrong. I don't want to go back. Not this time. blotted out. . . erased, but still there.

Hello there, the angel from my nightmare. The shadow in the background of the morgue. The unsuspecting victim of the darkness in the valley. We can live like Jack and Sally if we want. Where you can always find me. We'll have Halloween on Chrismas and in the night we'll wish this never ends.

I have a new favorite band! . . . Blink 182! *smile*

"I swear that I can go on forever again. Please let me know that my one bad day will end. I will go down as your lover, as your friend (parrallel!)"

Lunch is at 10:30 tomorrow. Why?

It's ok! No Spanish! EEE! though, I like that class. It's entertaining enough.

Are you afraid of being alone? 'cause I am.

Today I made children with Chris Avery. He's a very nice kid. We were flipping coins to decide what features our daughter had. She turned out pretty funny looking. I named her Haushinka. Sound familiar, Tito? Josh and Dairick are kind of annoying. They kept calling me over to their table. *sigh* Chris doesn't really like Josh.

But I didn't, I did, however, wake up with cat crap on the bottom of my bed *sigh*.

And my shot hurt like crazy.

And left over macaroni and cheese isn't good.

And there are people coming over so instead of going straight to bed, as I like to on days like this, I get to clean. Whee!

On the bright side, I did very well on my essay. *sigh* Tomorrow and Thursday, I will have nothing to do in 4th hour. 

Danielle and I are insane. Or. . . is anyone else ever convinced that someone is listening to your thoughts, so you think "Get out of my head!"? Maybe Nellie and I are weird.

Bryce looked good. (:. A lot of people ride my bus. . . a lot. And I know a ton of them, too. I made a new friend. . . Sean o Shawn. He's fun and wears all black. He had fishnet on. He dresses like the cheerleader does. This sounds like science fiction, but it's not. The woman who stars in this bizarre story--which is not from a supermarket tabloid, but rather the venerable New England Journal of Medicine--is now 52 years old. Her name is Jane. Jane had three sons, all grown now and all of whom were conceived and born the natural way. When one of them needed a kidney transplant, she learned that she--the mother--was not biologically related to her own child. Tests proved that to be true for two of her three sons. It's as if Jane conceived and gave birth to another woman's children. The study, which was more like an investigation, was led by Dr. Margot Kruskall of the Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center in Boston, Massachusetts. New Scientist reports that Kruskall concluded that Jane is a chimera, a mixture of two individuals. What happened is that Jane's mother conceived two non-identical twin sisters whose cells intermingled in the womb and instead of growing into two people, fused into a single body. The cells from one twin dominate in Jane's blood, but in other tissues, including her ovaries, cells from both twins live alongside each other. And that explains why two of her three sons have the genetics of Jane's fraternal twin. It's as if Jane gave birth to her unborn twin sister's children. There are about 30 instances of chimerism that have been reported worldwide.

GRR! You know, it calmed down for a while and we were getting along great. Chris has some sort of senser that tells him when I've had a good day just so he can ruin it for me. He unplugged the computer. Why? Because I didn't say 'ok' when he told me there was a light on in my room.

People are mean. Where are the koala bears?

I had a good day. Did you?

Well, my afternoon was good. . . We played a game to review for the test. I want to play the game again. It was fun. Only because my group won, though. Heheh. The 10 point question at the end was easy, but no one except me knew it. Turns out the answer to the last question was not 'do you like green eggs and ham?' hehe. He asked a sports question, so I put do you like green eggs and ham? But that's ok! Because we ended up with 18.5 points. :) AND Extra Credit. I'm glad for the extra credit. . . I don't have an A in that class anymore. Or in Spanish, either. I'll do extra credit in there but I don't know if it'll help. I have B's in 4/6 classes. SLACKER!!! Just like Cody calls me. Hey . . . *giggle* Dairick and Josh got extra credit today too. They're funny kids. I think they scare Chris. Chris was wearing my crown today. That's why we won. . . I think. Hehe. . . Hum. . . I was really hyper today. But then Bryce was being mean just a second ago so now I'm not. He's still upset with me, but will not tell me why. And he really is this time. . . EE! I got a 48/50 on my essay. I think the best way for me to judge the grade I'm going to recieve on my essays is by how little I like them. I hated both essays I've written so far this year. . . but I got really good grades on both. . . I was elated by my score, though :). Then my day just kept going up and up and up. I didn't see much of my friends, though. I'm thinking Mr.Tito is avoiding me. And Karin had NHS and Danielle was in Pottery. . . so I went into . . . surprise!. . . the journalism lab. It's a good thing I love that class. Because I am the least liked person there, so I would end up dropping out if I wasn't in love with it. That's me. I don't go where I'm not wanted. Unless they bluntly tell me I'm not wanted. Then I'll just stick around to annoy them :). . . Biology was great. We should have more classes like that. *chomp* Carrots are good. But not cooked carrots. Nellie should join journalism. Bryce wore a pretty shirt today. That picture ovver there has green eyelashes. I don't know why it's hanging up. It's my visual metaphor for kleffner. I think I'll hang it on the wall above my bed. I've started collecting little things from this year up there. Like all of my stories and pictures and awards and things. Well, award. I only have one :). I'll get another one at the end of the year. *giggle* I remember when I first got the computer I had a lot of fun making awards. Hehehehe. I wasn't the brightest kid. Broccoli is yummy. Do you like broccoli? I do. But I'm allergic to it. I ate all the broccoli Danielle and I bought. I felt really sick after. I think I should start reading those books that Karin loaned me. I kind of stole them from her and if they're here too long they'll get ruined. I'm going to go do that right now since. . . I DON'T HAVE HOMEWORK! EEEK! Except. . . I have 3 tests tomorrow *sigh*! OK! I'm going to go study now. I hope this entry amused you. Did it make sense? It seems sort of random and disorganized. Hehehe in Biology Chris got really annoyed with me. It was funny. I would write the right answer on the paper, then say the wrong answer. Heh, I'm rather fond of Chris. He's a nice kid and has neat hair. Does anyone else have him in any of their classes?

I want to be in a new place.

A place where I'm not known or thought of as Bryce's friend, or Danielle's friend or Chris's sister or Kent's daughter Alex. A place where I have a chance to be what I am. . . not what I used to be.

I try to explain to people what I mean, but they jump to their own conclusions about me.  They listen to half my side, then believe what they want to about me. They say I'm stubborn, but only because I won't go over to their side easily. Their not used to that. To them, their side is the right side and anyone who thinks otherwise is wrong, and stubborn when they won't believe their side, or the majority, right away. Just like today in Biology. I was sitting at my table and we were doing a chapter review. They both had one answser and I had a different one. They automatically assumed they were right and we argued over it for a while. Then I proved them wrong. Little things like that happen all the time. Or when Danielle and I were proofing the paper in the journalism lab. She went through and since every other headline was upstyle, she marked my page saying I should go to upstyle instead of downstyle. In the staff handbook it says headlines are to be written in downstyle. I don't do it to be different. If I thought majority was right in a particular case, I'd agree with them. Maybe I am stubborn, but so are they. That's just the way people are. They think one thing and they don't want to be proved wrong. None of you do.

Everyone around me is either growing further away from me or I can't stand to be around them anymore.

My mom never tells me what to do. Everyday she tells Katy and Chris to do chores, but she just ignores me. She never tells me to clean my room or brush my teeth or take a shower or do my homework. She tells Katy and Chris to do these things all the time. Katy and Chris have curfews and bedtimes and things, but I don't. It's funny, to complain about her trusting me too much.

My dad called tonight. He was disappointed when I answered. He hardly said anything to me. Just asked for anyone else and told me he moved into a motel and the room number, then hung up. He has stopped saying he loves me and everything. I don't understand why he loathes me so much. I don't get why any of my family does. I don't do anything to them. I'm too shy, so I hide. They accuse me of not making an effort, but how much of an effort do they make? Calling and when I answer asking for someone else right off. I know I don't reach out, but it would be nice if they recognized that they don't either.

Chris doesn't have a job anymore. So he has gone back to acting like a jerk around here and doing what he wants. The little things that he does make me so mad. And he gets mad at me, too. Like, when I don't jump up right away. I was reading earlier and he got mad when I wouldn't drop the book and show him something on the computer right away.

Danielle and I hardly ever talk anymore, and I should be sad about this. But I'm not, and it's not because I don't like her. I love her to death. It's because I want to be alone, so us not talking is making that that much easier for me.

Bryce is mad at me again. I don't know what to say about that because I don't understand what he's mad about. FYI, Bryce, I don't think it's an act.

I've started to loathe Mr. Balsai's class more and more. Karin said "Why? Because he makes you think?" HAH! People only believe he makes us think. He's such a hypocrite. He's telling us what to think, not how to think. He's spouting off his own ideas and views, hoping we'll take that and start believing it, hoping we'll swallow it and regurgitate in our own words and so-called own opinions. I'm not swallowing. I'm choking on them. He hides it so well that everyone honestly believes what he's saying is right and when they repeat it, it's their ideas, not his. It makes me sick to see him create mini-hypocrites. Everyone does it. Everyone is trying to convince you that their way is the right way. Whether they play like Balsai and hide that behind some cheap rhetoric or not is up to them.

I feel sorry for people. I feel sorry for the way they think and feel and act. This includes myself. We're not real. We don't have dimension. What I'm saying is not real. What I'm saying is the words of thousands of men before me. I took the idea because I thought it sounded 'cool' and I reworded it so now it's 'pretty' and I'm posting it for you all to see. They're not my words. They told me what to believe and I put it together to relate to the present. They're not my words. Bryce asked tonight why I'm so negative. Well, if you just stopped and looked around, saw the world from my eyes, and I'm sure a lot of other people's eyes, because I can't be the only one who sees it, you'd know why I am so negative. People are so cheap, and they'll take anything they're fed.

I want to be in a new place. A place where I don't have to feel guilty for who I am. A place where I don't have to hesitate to post this because it's not all positive and will, no doubt, offend the masses. Well, screw that. Go ahead, tell me how I'm wrong.

A blank piece of paper scares me.

"Everything that holds me together is starting to fall apart"

I had a good day! EEK!

Not like one of those days when it starts out good then ends badly like most good days. My day has been good from start to finish. *scratches nose*

Want to hear about it? I didn't think so! but I'll tell you anyway.

When we got to school we had to wait for Mrs. Balls to get there. We went to Mr.Balsai's classroom and talked to Karin. Her hair was pulled back today. Muy bonita! She's always muy bonita, but she doesn't like to hear it. She's also smart, too. The paper boy gave me bad genes.

When Mrs. Balls go to school we talked to her, and she seems pretty excited to have Danielle join staff. Maybe because I told her Danellie is my best friend and she's just happy that I have friends.  She also said she likes what I'm doing for the paper. cool!

Then Mr. Balsai's class was boring, as usual. The best day in his class was when he wrote 'why' up on the board and had us answer.

More people said I'm cute. I'M NOT! I'm hot! Like a turkey! Jeeze!

I failed my math test. But I don't feel bad. Everyone did. Well, one person got a C, but everyone else failed. I'm assuming I'm one of the failers. Math isn't my strongest subject.

I sold my ad for next issue! WHEE! Yay! Mrs. Novak is even going to tell Julie no because it's already been sold to me. I'm so happy! I'm beginning to like Mrs. Novak. She's really easy. Like her class is super easy and she's very nice and she runs the student store so we get out, like, 10 minutes early on days when she has some food in the store since we're fourth hour. That happened yesterday. And tomorrow, too. My grade in that class is good.

I spent lunch with Mr. Bryce. I scared the kid out of the restroom. I feel bad for that. And I made Kelvin feel badly, too. How do I do it, when Bryce is ten times meaner to Kelvin than I am? I don't think his friends like me very much. They came up and were all over him, then looked over and saw me and were like 'lets go' and all piled off. Hm. . . Do I smell badly?

Fifth hour was fun. Got made fun of for to do my work. I like that new kid. . . Chris. He's very nice and doesn't mind sitting with Sam and I, who are freaks. He actually likes us. Heather and Liz think he's. . . uhm. . . very good looking. Those girls are ALWAYS talking about guys. I told Tony and Deirick that I'm a guy and I'm gay. Tony freaked out. . . *smile*. You should have seen him. It was very funny.

I was very very hyper after school and my grade in Spanish has dropped 11% in a week. I asked a bunch of people if they were happy. The girl on the bike is!

When I got home chris was making me mad so I went into my room, played AFI and played my bass in the dark. I tore up my fingers, but it was very therepeutic. . . 

WHHHEEEEEE! That 70s Show!

You know you're a child of the '80s if. . . (bolded ones apply) 1. You've ever ended a sentence with the word "PSYCH!" 2. You watched the Pound Puppies. 3. You can sing the rap to the "Fresh Prince of Bel Air." I used to be able to, anyway. . . 4. You wore biker shorts under your skirts and felt stylish. 5. You yearned to be a member of the Baby-Sitters Club and tried to start a club of your own. (It's not something I'm proud of!) 6. You owned those lil Strawberry Shortcake pals scented dolls. 7. You know that "WOAH" comes from Joey on Blossom. (I do now. . . does that count?) 8. Two words: M.C. Hammer. 9. If you ever watched "Fraggle Rock." 10. You had plastic streamers on your handle bars. 11. You can sing the entire theme song to "Duck Tales." (I can sing along. . .) 12. You remember when it was actually worth getting up early on a Saturday to watch cartoons. 13. You wore a ponytail on the side of your head. 14. 01. I love dying my hair.

15. I'm extremely facetious and sarcastic.
16. I tend to argue just for the sake of arguing. Not really for blood, but I'll argue points that I disagree with just to argue, in time I'll begin corrupting myself into believing the point that I'm arguing for.
17. I am very manipulative. This includes with myself. I can twist something into something anyone would believe was true.
18. During the summer I love staying up all night just to take a walk in the morning. I go to the park or something and I swing. Once I picked up garbage around the park just because I loved the atmosphere of the morning and had nothing better to do.
19. I am an insomniac
20. I get everything I ask for and everything I get, I've asked for. Like with my friends and the way I allow them to step all over me. I ask them to use me as a pillow to land on when they fall backward, but get mad when they use me as the safety net.

22. I live in the past which is probably why I love history so much.
23. I am the strangest procrastinator ever. I eat to avoid doing homework and I clean to avoid eating.
24. I hate silence and I tend to babble my head off when I get nervous. Making people believe I'm a freak.
25. I am a freak.
26. I despise when Bryce asks why I like him. Mostly because I don't know how to answer it.

If you said that you want me around because I'm your friend, I would drop it and never mention leaving again. I can't help doing the fishing thing, it always just . . . happens.
28. I can only sleep through loud noises in Math class. That class puts me to sleep.
29. I am a heretic.
30. I save aim conversations.
31. People love my bluntness when I compliment them, but hate it when I insult them.
32. I am a macroverbumsciolist. And I like it!
33. A day doesn't go by when someone doesn't call me cute. It drives me nuts, but I like it all the same.
34. Sadistic music makes me giggle. "Swallow choke and DIE!"
35. I love the smell of matches.
36. When someone hints something to me, I'll understand it but be too afraid that I'm wrong to let them know that I understood.
37. My hygene habits are a lot different than most females of my age and I spend hardly any time in front of the mirror.
38. I am overprotective of Bryce. A lot more protective than I am of me. And I get really worried about him sometimes even though he can take care of himself a lot better than I can.
39. I LOATHE hanging around Bryce, Karin, and Danielle at any one time in any combination. It really brings out the worst in me.
40. I love being the cute, sweet, innocent girl I am and I love the attention it gets me, but I still complain about it.
41. I say a lot of things I don't mean and hurt a lot of people when I do. Then I try to take it back but they won't listen. I don't blame them, though.
42. I love confrontation.
43. I can't resist reflective surfaces!
44. I'm the clumsiest person you will ever meet.

I'm out to change the world on this, and I know it's not going to work, but I just need the chance to prove that I'm as good as everyone else even though I refuse to conform to society's rules about how one should dress *gag* I hate the way other people dress anyway.
46. Emo music makes me really really happy.
47. Rock music depresses me. Seriously depresses me.
48. I have a really good long-term memory but a terrible short-term memory and it's the most obnoxious thing ever, I think it scares some people.
49. Danielle isn't the only person who has never gotten high or drunk. The difference between the two of us is I don't have any desire to do either, she's curious.
50. I get easily infatuated with people, but very seldom do I actually like them.
51. I realized today that I am a huge flirt. I don't meant to. I just kind of end up flirting.
52. I'm hot like a turkey
53. I have tons of quirks.
54. I'm really easy going.
55. I am a completely different person around my family.

58. I laugh at my own jokes.
59. Laughter makes me laugh.
60. I love to jump up and down in public. Like at concerts or dances. I can't dance so I jump up and down. It's fun!
61. Sometimes I'll catch myself doing something I hadn't planned to do, like dancing, or twirling in circles or talking to myself. Often I'll catch myself after someone is always staring at me like I'm a freak.
62. I'm a freak.
63. I really do care what people think. I just want to be seen differently than most people would want to be seen.
64. I can't retain water. If I drink any more than 8 ounces in 2 hours, I'll be in the bathroom every five minutes. It's obnoxious. I can never get my recommended 8 glasses of water and I'm always dehydrated.
65. Danielle and I are obsessed with making 4-year plans. I think at the end of 2nd semester senior year, we'll finally have one that we won't end up changing.
66. I desperately want to take every English class offered, but there aren't enough hours in the day.
67. I can never learn too much and I think I'm going to be a forever-college student crashing on Karin's couch.
68. I am in love with Journalism.
69. I tend to love things that I'm good at.
70. I take abuse from everyone. I think this is something that I got from years of my dad physically and emotionally abusing mom and us kids. Statistics say I'm more likely to have abusive relationships. I love everyone too much, though, to tell them when they're hurting me.
71. I don't fall in and out of like very easily.
72. I'm terrible at taking and giving hints.
73. I refuse to sell Bryce my halloween candy. I don't care how much he begs.
74. Chris does the smallest things that can piss me off to no end. I'm watching Roseanne right now and he turned it down, so I turned it back up, then I left the computer and he turned the screen off. It made my blood pressure skyrocket.
75. I once tried, unsuccessfully, to be a vegitarian. Now that I lost the title, I rarely eat meat.
76. I get very little sleep at night. I got about 4 hours last night.
77. My alarm clock doesn't wake me up anymore.
78. I, like Danielle, push friends away until I give in and they become my friend. I don't mean to. . . I don't even notice I'm doing it. I just don't know how to act around people.
79. My cat is crazy. She just ran head first into my leg.
80. I often aide in the cheating of others. Err. . . I let people copy my work and I give them all the answers if I figure them out.
